<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="39" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                        <head>39. Telegram 400 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d39fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–655.
                                Confidential. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-06">August 6, 1955, 2:41
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d39-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d39-1"/>
                        <p>400. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Do you have any clue as to source Scripps-Howard dispatch Geneva August 4
                            written by Ludwell Denny? On surface some of information would appear to
                            be from American official source.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>